to list all the files in a directory

ls

ls means list

to a more clean view:

ls -ls

or

ls -l

to save the list of files in a text:

ls > listfile.txt

to list all files (included hidden ones):

ls -a


if you are in antother folder you can always user list command for other paths like:

ls /home/myuser

and you will get the list of files without moving from you current folder
